li><a href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/mags/design\">设计匠艺</a></li> \n                  <li><a href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/articles/weekly\">一周拾遗</a></li>                  \n                </ul>\n              </li>\n              \n               <li class=\"dropdown  \">\n                <a href=\"#\" class=\"dropdown-toggle\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\">更多 <b class=\"caret\"></b></a>\n                <ul class=\"dropdown-menu\">\n                  <li><a href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/bbs\">讨论区</a></li>  \n                  <li><a href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/about\">关于我们</a></li>                 \n                </ul>\n              </li>\n              \n              </ul>\n            <form class=\"navbar-search pull-left\" action=\"http://www.tuicool.com/search\">\n              <input type=\"text\" class=\"search-query span2\" name=\"kw\" placeholder=\"搜索\">\n            </form>\n            <ul class=\"nav pull-right\">\n                <li><a href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/login\">登录</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </nav>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n  </div>   \n</div>\n  <div id =\"flash_container\" class=\"noPrint\">    \n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"container-fluid\">  \n    <div class=\"frd_pos\">\n    <div class=\"row-fluid\" style=\"margin-top: 15px\">\n        <div>\n            <script type=\"text/javascript\">BAIDU_CLB_fillSlot(\"1076478\");</script>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row-fluid article_row_fluid\">\n    <div class=\"span8 contant article_detail_bg\">\n        <h1>Breaking Away From The Me Too Crowd</h1>\n        <div class=\"article_meta\">\n            <span class=\"timestamp\">时间&nbsp;2015-05-18 20:59:31\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"from\">\n                <i class=\"icon-globe\"></i>\n                    <a class=\"cut cut28 from\" href=\"/sites/QjqyU3\" target=\"_blank\">AdrienneSmith\n                    </a>\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"source\" style=\"display:block;\"><i style=\"float:left;\">原文</i>&nbsp; \n                <a class=\"cut cut70\" href=\"http://www.tuicool.com/articles/goto?id=z6vINr2\" style=\"display:inline-block;\">http://www.adriennesmith.net/breaking-away-me-too-crowd/</a>\n            </span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"article_body\" id=\"nei\">\n            <div> \n <p> <img src=\"http://img1.tuicool.com/2MvyUr.png\" class=\"alignCenter\" /> <em>I’m so thrilled to have with me this month someone that I really think a lot of.</em> </p> \n <p>Richard is someone I met of course through blogging but because of the relationship that we’ve built he has definitely been there for me and he knows how much he can count on me as well.</p> \n <p>I love what he does over at his blog, I admire the person that he is and he’s someone I will always highly recommend.</p> \n <p> <em>I’m excited about the topic he’s sharing with us today too so I hope you’ll enjoy this one as much as I did reading through it.</em> </p> \n <p>One of my favourite spectacles in the UK is during the onset of winter. If there’s a crisp, blue sky, and you are located out of the bigger cities, chances are you will see quite a breath-taking site in the sky above.</p> \n <p>Thousands and thousands of birds in the sky, sometimes flying in a magical formation, migrating to warmer climes where there is more light, and most importantly, more food.</p> \n <p>I love it when they fly in a triangular type of formation. One bird leading the rest. If you’ve ever seen this, it’s quite mesmerizing to watch, I’m sure you’ll agree.</p> \n <p>But every time I see such a spectacle in the sky above me, I’m always on the lookout for the one thing that amazes me even more.</p> \n <p>Sometimes, the formation will break. And a small handful of these birds will break off from the back, and go their own route. It rarely happens, but when it does, it always leaves me wondering about life in general, and most relevant to this post, blogging.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>Choosing Your Own Route</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>The start of 2015 heralded a new direction for me.</p> \n <p>Previously, I was partly indoctrinated in the ‘Me Too’ crowd. Not fully, but I was prone to follow, rather than lead.</p> \n <p>I decided to change that when the clocks struck midnight on New Years Eve..</p> \n <p>I openly admit that in part, I was guided by the masses. You know what I mean here. Where the majority says this is the best strategy to achieve x, y or z result. Then I’d probably look into it, agree, and then write about it, without offering much in the way of authorial presence or opinion.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>Does this sound familiar to you?</b> </span> </h2> \n <p> And here’s what it boiled down to. I wanted to be accepted. I wanted to be safe. I didn’t want to leave mycomfort zone. I didn’t want to upset my readers. I didn’t want to go against the status quo. And I didn’t want to knock down important relationships that I had worked hard to build up. </p> \n <p>And while it’s sometimes not something deliberate we set out to do, we can’t help it. When you read the same thing with the same angle from many people you trust and respect, sometimes it’s hard not to absorb that angle.</p> \n <p>And suddenly, their way of thinking, and their opinion, is photosynthesized into our own opinion.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>Sticking Your Head Above The Parapet</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>I want you to ask yourself a question.</p> \n <p>Have you ever drafted a post in WordPress, or started writing a comment, only then to delete the whole thing?</p> \n <p>“I can’t write that”, you probably thought.</p> \n <p>“If I put that view across, I’m going to alienate my readers”, you may have thought.</p> \n <p>I’ve been there. I have sat and re-read my post a hundred times asking myself those exact questions. And each time, I’ve always gone ahead and hit that publish button.</p> \n <p>And you should too, because…</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>It’s Your Blog. It’s Your Voice.</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>So use it.</p> \n <p> When you’ve written a post and you’re hovering over the publish button, almost afraid of releasing your content to the world, you’ll know at that moment that you’reusing your own voice. You know at that moment that you’re that migrating bird who’s about to break off from the rest of the group. </p> \n <p>Seriously, don’t be afraid of it. Don’t be afraid of putting your own opinion across. Just because Mr Authority Blogger says something, doesn’t mean you have to agree.</p> \n <p>If you have a belief or opinion that goes against the tide, try sticking your head above that parapet. Try going against the swing. I’ve done it twice already this year.</p> \n <p>Is it a coincidence that those posts are amongst the most read posts on my blog? Is it a coincidence that those posts have seen the most engagement through social shares and comments? I don’t think so.</p> \n <p>Most of you will be familiar with this popular phrase that came from the mouths of our teachers during our school days:</p> \n <p>“If you have a question, no matter how daft it sounds, ask it. Because the likelihood is that others have the same question but are just too afraid to raise their hand.”</p> \n <p>The same notion can be extended to blogging. If you have something to say that you think is slightly risqu&eacute;, just say it. It’s likely that others feel the same as you.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>Someone Else’s Blog. But It’s Still Your Voice</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>This really does extend right out of your blog, to the comments you leave on other people’s blogs. I think it’s really important that you do this. Sometimes I don’t agree with things I read on other blogs. Nowadays, I’m far more confident in offering a true opinion.</p> \n <p>The main thing is when going against the flow, is to do it in a courteous and polite manner. It’s really important to respect the blog that you are commenting on, and put across your point carefully and in a constructive manner.</p> \n <p>Which leads me into another question for you.</p> \n <p>Have you ever just agreed with a blog post through a comment you have left, rather than writing what you’ve really thought?</p> \n <p>I’ll level with you here. I think you have, because I have. Because it’s much easier just to agree and move on, than offer a vastly different opinion to what is offered in the post.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>3 Key Tips When Going Against The Flow</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>There are dangers associated with removing yourself from the ‘Me Too’ crowd. But I strongly believe the rewards far outweigh the dangers.</p> \n <p>Below are 3 simple tips to reduce the risks involved:</p> \n <p>1. Be polite and courteous.</p> \n <p>There’s a danger that you may come across rude, intrusive or even arrogant. Always remain polite and courteous whether you are writing on your own blog, or in a comment on someone else’s. Remember, it’s probably not your opinion that will turn readers off you or alienate them; it’s the way you put it across.</p> \n <p>2. Be Truthful With Yourself…And Your Audience</p> \n <p>Whatever you do, don’t just go against the grain because you feel like it. Don’t go and write a controversial piece for your blog on the back of reading this post. You have to mean it. You have to have a true belief in what you are saying.</p> \n <p>3. Accept Other’s Point Of View</p> \n <p>I’m not always right. You’re not always right. But that’s the beauty of the internet, and the beauty of blogging. A plethora of mixed opinions and mixed emotions. Embrace a different viewpoint instead of fighting against it, but do still stand firm on your own beliefs.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>My Final Thoughts</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>While common sense says that if everyone is saying a certain something, then it’s probably right, it doesn’t mean that it’s right all of the time. And it doesn’t mean that you always have to agree with it.</p> \n <p>And while I’m not advocating a policy of controversy throughout your blog, I am suggesting that we all need to clear our minds now and again, and say what we really think, instead of choosing the easier route of following the thoughts of others within our niche or industry.</p> \n <p>It’s what makes us different. And it’s what makes us unique.</p> \n <h2> <span> <b>What’s Your Thoughts?</b> </span> <b></b> </h2> \n <p>I would love to hear your thoughts on my post in the comments section below.</p> \n <p>Have you been part of the ‘Me Too’ crowd?</p> \n <p>Maybe you have been like me, and decided not to publish that post that you have just written or submit that blog comment?</p> \n <p>Whatever your thoughts, I’d be extremely grateful to hear them, and I’ll make sure I respond to every single one of them.</p> \n</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"article_social\">\n        <div class=\"article_like\">\n                <button class=\"btn btn-large btn-like\" id=\"my_like2\" data_id=\"z6vINr2\">\n                    <i class=\"icon-heart-empty\"></i>\n                    赞一个\n                </button>\n                <button class=\"btn btn-large btn-fav liked\" id=\"my_like\" data_id=\"z6vINr2\">\n                    <i class=\"icon-star-empty\"></i>\n                    收 藏\n                </button>\n        </div>\n        </div>\n           <div id=\"site_articles\">\n              <div class=\"article-part-title\">\n                <span>推荐文章</span>\n              </div>\n          <ul class=\"side_article_list\">\n                <li class=\"side_article_list_item\">\n                    1.<a href=\"/articles/ZbUF7zJ\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Google’s Phantom Is Exposed and DID Happen – But It Was About Quality Signals\">\n                    Google’s Phantom Is Exposed and DID Happen – But It Was About..\n                </a>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"side_article_list_item\">\n                    2.<a href=\"/articles/eqMBZz6\" target=\"_